         <abstract>
            <p>Let M = 2&lt;sup&gt;w&lt;/sup&gt;, and G&lt;sub&gt;M&lt;/sub&gt; = {1, 3, ..., M - 1}. A sequence {y&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;}, y&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt; âˆˆ G&lt;sub&gt;M&lt;/sub&gt;, is obtained by the formula &lt;tex-math&gt;$y_{n + 1} \equiv a\overline y_n + b + cy_n \operatorname{mod} M$&lt;/tex-math&gt;. The sequence {x&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;}, x&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt; = y&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;/M, is a sequence of pseudorandom numbers of the maximal period length M/2 if and only if &lt;tex-math&gt;$a + c \equiv 1 (\operatorname{mod} 4), b \equiv 2 (\operatorname{mod} 4)$&lt;/tex-math&gt;. In this note, the uniformity is investigated by the 2-dimensional serial test for the sequence. We follow closely the method of papers by Eichenauer-Herrmann and Niederreiter.</p>
          </abstract>
